 {"id":"bd-9zdo","title":"rt_sigtimedwait complementary coverage: no-pending timeout + siginfo inspection","description":"Cod's bd-w9gx fix (commit 53ee112) added 2 rt_sigtimedwait tests (zero-timeout delivery of pending signal, invalid-tv_nsec EINVAL). Coverage gaps: (1) zero-timeout with NO matching signal pending must return EAGAIN (symmetric negative case), (2) when a signal IS delivered, the siginfo_t buffer must be populated with si_signo == signo (zeroed buffer would allow a silent kernel ABI drift). Add both tests complementary to cod's existing pair. Scope: crates/frankenlibc-core/tests/syscall_veneer_test.rs.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-20T21:32:53.122428665Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-20T21:34:31.255018865Z","closed_at":"2026-04-20T21:34:31.253076988Z","close_reason":"Added 2 rt_sigtimedwait complements in commit 413d85d: zero-timeout-no-pending-returns-EAGAIN (symmetric to cod's delivery case) and populates-siginfo-signo (inspects siginfo_t that cod's test wrote but never read). Together with cod's 2 tests, full 4-quadrant coverage of the sync signal-wait syscall.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
